text: Anchomomys' milleri is an extinct primate related to lemuriforms that lived in Africa during the early late Eocene. It was originally thought to be a member of the European genus Anchomomys, but was later aligned with the djebelemurids, although a new generic name needs to be assigned. == References == Category:Prehistoric strepsirrhines Category:Eocene primates Category:Fossil taxa described in 1997 Category:Eocene mammals of Africa
title: 'Anchomomys' milleri
